  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the artichokes and the heart of palm."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Mash the heart of palm with a fork or potato masher until it’s combined into a chunky mashed texture. Place into a large bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tear the artichoke into flakes and add to the bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely slice the celery and shallot."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add celery, shallot, and seasonings to the bowl, mix and season with salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Form patties with the mixture, they should be about 4cm in diameter."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Put the patties on a tray and let them chill in the fridge while you make the mayo."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Blitz the nori in a food processor to a flaky powder. Add that powder to the mayo with a squeeze of lemon and mix through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When the patties have chilled for at least 10 mins, prepare your ingredients for frying. In three separate bowls, add the flour, milk and breadcrumbs. Dip each patty first into the flour and dust off any excess. Then into the milk and finally into the breadcrumbs. Ensure they’re covered fully for an even fry."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Fry the patties for 3-4 mins on each side, until just browned and crispy. Alternatively, you can deep-fry the patties until they are golden brown. You can also bake them at 180°C for 20 mins, spray with oil first. Best served immediately."
    }
  ],
